See https://github.com/TrevorPilley/MicroLite.Extensions.WebApi/releases for a summary of changes made in this release of the package.
Net.Http.WebApi.OData 3.5.0 changes: - Removed types/members obsoleted in 3.4.x and earlier - Expression QueryNode objects refactored (partly for performance, partly to simplify) - Improved validation - Fixed parsing of DateTimeOffset - Correctly returning HTTP 400 and HTTP 501 where appropriate instead of ODataException which resulted in HTTP 500 - SelectQueryOption and ExpandQueryOption merged into SelectExpandQueryOption since they have the same implementation - Introduction of EdmProperty which is used in SelectExpandQueryOption, OrderByProperty, PropertyAccessNode - The InlineCount<T> class was still returning OData 2.0 format { "__count":0, "results":[] }, updated to OData 3.0 format { "odata.count":0, "value":[] } replaced by PagedResult<T> class

Net.Http.WebApi.OData 4.0.0 changes: - Removed types/members obsoleted in 3.4.x and earlier - Expression QueryNode objects refactored (partly for performance, partly to simplify) - Improved validation - Fixed parsing of DateTimeOffset - Correctly returning HTTP 400 and HTTP 501 where appropriate instead of ODataException which resulted in HTTP 500 - SelectQueryOption and ExpandQueryOption merged into SelectExpandQueryOption since they have the same implementation - Introduction of EdmProperty which is used in SelectExpandQueryOption, OrderByProperty, PropertyAccessNode - The InlineCount<T> class was still returning OData 2.0 format { "__count":0, "results":[] }, updated to OData 4.0 format { "@odata.count":0, "value":[] } replaced by PagedResult<T> class - SubStringOf removed - Contains added - DateTime & Time removed - Date and TimeOfDay added (don't require prefixing) - DateTimeOffset parsing improved, also doesn't require prefix - Guid doesn't require prefix - $inlinecount=allpages replaced by $count=true - Added $search query option - Added FractionalSeconds, Now, MinDateTime and MaxDateTime functions
